INFORMATION (DIFFERENCE BETWEEN > AND >>)

ðŸ”¹ > (Single Greater Than) â€” Output Redirection (Truncate)
What it does: Redirects standard output to a file, overwriting the file if it already exists.

Example:
echo "hello" > file.txt

âœ… Creates file.txt (if not existing)
âœ… Writes "hello" into it
âŒ Erases any previous content in file.txt

ðŸ”¹ >> (Double Greater Than) â€” Output Redirection (Append)
What it does: Redirects standard output to a file, appending to the file if it already exists.

Example:
echo "world" >> file.txt

âœ… Creates file.txt (if not existing)
âœ… Adds "world" at the end of the existing content
âœ… Preserves existing data